<body id="tribute-info">
    <h2> Here's a timeline of Allen Iverson's life: </h2>
    <ul>
        <li> <b>Born:</b> June 7, 1975 </li>
        <li> <b>1992/1993:</b> Led Bethel High School to Virginia state championships in both basketball & football.</li>
        <li> <b>1994:</b> Left home to attend Georgetown University & play for legendary basketball coach John Thompson.</li>
        <li> <b>1995:</b> Won the Big East Rookie of the Year award & led Georgetown to the Sweet 16 Round of the NCAA tournament.</li>
        <li> <b>1996:</b> Led Georgetown to a Big East championship & the Elite 8 round of the NCAA tournament.</li>
        <li> <b>1996:</b> Selected first overall by the Philadelphia 76ers in the NBA draft.</li>
        <li> <b>1997:</b> Won the NBA's Rookie of the Year Award.</li>
        <li> <b>2001:</b> Won the NBA's MVP Award.</li>
        <li> <b>2005:</b> Won the NBA's All-Star Game MVP Award.</li>
        <li> <b>2006:</b> Was traded to the Denver Nuggets.</li>
        <li> <b>2009:</b> Returned to the Philadelphia 76ers.</li>
        <li> <b>2013:</b> Officially retired from the NBA.</li>
        <li> <b>2016:</b> Was inducted into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame.</li>
    </ul>
    <p> "I don't want to be another Jordan, Magic, or Isiah. When my career is over, I want to be able to look in the mirror and say 'I did it my way'."<br>
        --Allen Iverson
    </p>
    </ul>
</body>

<footer>If you have time, you should read more about the great Allen Iverson on his <a id="tribute-link" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allen_Iverson">Wikipedia page.</a></footer>
